# Idempotency and Concurrency

- **Idempotency:** Design pipeline steps so that re-running with the same inputs is safe: same outcome, no duplicate side effects (e.g. double writes). Use "already ran" or skip logic where re-execution would be redundant.
- **Concurrency:** If multiple workers might run the same job or touch the same resources, document whether the design assumes single-worker execution or requires locking or distributed coordination. Avoid assuming "only one runner" without stating it; add locking or guards when the design requires it.
